<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
You have been a good friend of mine for a long time now, and I have enjoyed the discussions we have had. Please, don't message me in game anymore, I don't want to hear from you. Your superior, pious attitude makes me sick to bne honest, how dare you dictate to the entire body of Mages that we should not be able to finally, after all this waiting - two years in the making - receive new upgraded pets and a genuine nuke upgrade.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don´t see me dictating anywhere. I stated my personal opinion and if you cannot accept it, it cannot be helped. If you call yourself an good friend you wouldn´t start personal attacks but you would discuss it like a grown-up.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
We've been playing the same game as you, we've done it just as hard as you. Just because you are in an upper tier raiding guild means you get to say what we do and do not deserve in a new expansion?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Most people do NOT raid as hard as me or invest as much time as me. Should they be allowed to have fun? Sure. Should they be able to get upgrades? Sure. Should everyone hold the same power as the person who invests as much time as i do? No.<br>
<br>
Compare it to every RPG you want - you always need to invest time to become more powerful. Not so in PoP. You simply pickup a parchment and turn it in.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
I am honestly stunned that you could so brazenly come out and say such a thing. You strike down your own class mates! I know The Companions made out like bandits on the Tribunal from spell drop sales in Luclin, I paid over 40k to you guys for mine, and the current rumour is that you guys gleaned well over one million platinum pieces in spell sales alone. Is this the problem? Mandoman not able to line the guild coffers this time because we can actually go out and get our own damn spells without having to pay you guys?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Hogfather, you´re beginning to bore me at this point to be honest. Now you´re angry because you had to buy spells at one time of the game? You could have also bought them easily from EV, RNG, SI or AN. If you bought them from us it means we sold them for less than the other guilds. I don´t even know what this has to do with the melee vs caster discussion.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Damn you to hell. Personal attack yes, but damn you Cyricus. You can use your admin powers and ban me form the board if you want, I could care less. If this is what the moderators have come to here, if this is what the Tower stands for, keeping the average joe mage down, then I want nothing of it. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Nice little speech, but even if i was a moderator i would not ban you over this. I just find it sad that you have to start personal attacks just because someone has a different opinion.<br>
<br>
