<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Strong words Hogfeather, but I agree it sounds like Cyruis wants not only better equipement, better effects, better pets (hello gloves of dark summoning), but wants to ensure that no magician but people that raid in the top guilds should ever get anything without them SELLING it to you.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I never cared much for pp. In fact the money i made i got from killing hundreds of Gornits and Hill Giants. The effects i have on my items are the same effects you have: focus items which are mage summoned at lvl 61 offer the same effects as items which are dropping in Vex Thal.<br>
<br>
Again: I don´t know who brought it up, but selling stuff is the most unimportant thing in EQ for me.<br>
